What you need to know:

After a series of thefts by staffers between 2001 and 2016 coupled with poor management decisions, Uchumi Supermarkets is now hoping that Mohamed will get the retailer out of its deathbed.Uchumi is the first firm in Kenya to undergo a CVA, after 152 creditors voted to allow the retailer a chance to come back to life.Working capital is money used to fill the shelves and ensure that day-to-day operations continue normally.